** sch_path: /foss/designs/cdac/caps.sch
* ============================================================
* CDAC ARRAY STRUCTURE / SAMPLE-AND-HOLD SIZING
* ============================================================
* Architecture: split-array CDAC, 10-bit, GF180MCU cap_mim_2f0fF (2fF/um^2).
*   MSB array (node Vx):     C6..C10, weights 1:1:2:4:8  (16 unit caps)
*   LSB array (node Vx_lsb): C1..C5,  weights 1:1:2:4:8  (16 unit caps)
*   Bridge cap:               C11 (upsized unit, 4.13um x 4.13um vs the
*                              4um x 4um unit elsewhere) sets the LSB-array
*                              attenuation ratio seen from Vx.
*   Unit cell: 4um x 4um -> Cu ~= 35.65 fF (per cap_mim_2f0fF model eqns:
*              c_c0 = c_cox*area + c_capsw*peri, nominal corner/mismatch).
*
* THESE ARRAY CAPACITORS ARE THE SAMPLE-AND-HOLD CAPACITORS.
*   There is no dedicated/separate S/H cap in this design. Each unit cap's
*   bottom plate is switched by its "transistors" cell (see transistors.spice)
*   between Vin (phi_s=1, SAMPLE phase) and VREF/GND per Dx/Dx_b (phi_s=0,
*   HOLD/REDISTRIBUTE phase). See transistors.spice header for the full
*   two-phase description.
*
* kT/C NOISE SIZING (see ktc_noise_budget.py for the full derivation/margin):
*   Effective sampling cap at Vx (MSB array + LSB array/bridge series comb.)
*     ~= 606 fF
*   kT/C noise (T=300K)            ~= 82.7 uVrms
*   10-bit quantization noise, VREF=1.8V, LSB/sqrt(12)  ~= 507.4 uVrms
*   Margin: quantization noise is ~6.1x the kT/C noise floor, i.e. kT/C
*   noise is comfortably NOT the dominant noise term (>3x margin target).
*   Minimum effective cap for 3x margin would be ~145 fF -- current sizing
*   has ~4.2x more capacitance than that floor, at the cost of settling
*   time/switch sizing tradeoffs (see caps_tb.spice .meas for timing impact).
* ============================================================
**.subckt caps Vin GND VREF Vx phi_s VDD Dx_b<0> Dx<0> Dx_b<1> Dx_b<2> Dx_b<3> Dx_b<4> Dx_b<5> Dx_b<6> Dx_b<7> Dx_b<8> Dx_b<9>
*+ Dx<1> Dx<2> Dx<3> Dx<4> Dx<5> Dx<6> Dx<7> Dx<8> Dx<9> Vx_lsb
*.ipin Vin
*.ipin GND
*.ipin VREF
*.opin Vx
*.ipin phi_s
*.ipin VDD
*.ipin Dx_b<0>
*.ipin Dx<0>
*.ipin Dx_b<1>
*.ipin Dx_b<2>
*.ipin Dx_b<3>
*.ipin Dx_b<4>
*.ipin Dx_b<5>
*.ipin Dx_b<6>
*.ipin Dx_b<7>
*.ipin Dx_b<8>
*.ipin Dx_b<9>
*.ipin Dx<1>
*.ipin Dx<2>
*.ipin Dx<3>
*.ipin Dx<4>
*.ipin Dx<5>
*.ipin Dx<6>
*.ipin Dx<7>
*.ipin Dx<8>
*.ipin Dx<9>
*.opin Vx_lsb
XC1 net2 Vx_lsb cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=1
XC2 net1 Vx_lsb cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=1
XC3 net3 Vx_lsb cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=2
XC4 net4 Vx_lsb cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=4
XC5 net5 Vx_lsb cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=8
XC6 net6 Vx cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=1
XC7 net7 Vx cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=1
XC8 net8 Vx cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=2
XC9 net9 Vx cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=4
XC10 net10 Vx cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4e-6 c_length=4e-6 m=8
XC11 Vx_lsb Vx cap_mim_2f0fF c_width=4.13e-6 c_length=4.13e-6 m=1
x1 VDD Dx<0> Dx_b<0> phi_s VREF Vin net2 GND transistors
x2 VDD Dx<1> Dx_b<1> phi_s VREF Vin net1 GND transistors
x3 VDD Dx<4> Dx_b<4> phi_s VREF Vin net5 GND transistors
x4 VDD Dx<2> Dx_b<2> phi_s VREF Vin net3 GND transistors
x5 VDD Dx<3> Dx_b<3> phi_s VREF Vin net4 GND transistors
x6 VDD Dx<5> Dx_b<5> phi_s VREF Vin net6 GND transistors
x8 VDD Dx<7> Dx_b<7> phi_s VREF Vin net8 GND transistors
x9 VDD Dx<6> Dx_b<6> phi_s VREF Vin net7 GND transistors
x10 VDD Dx<8> Dx_b<8> phi_s VREF Vin net9 GND transistors
x11 VDD Dx<9> Dx_b<9> phi_s VREF Vin net10 GND transistors
**.ends

